data.body:
This PR introduces runtime resource -> cache mapping with support for overloaded resource types.  Given a FBX in the project at Resources/Models/Robo_01.fbx, the following code could be used to access it and setup animations/materials from script:

``` csharp
var roboNode = scene.CreateChild("Roboman");
var roboModel = roboNode.CreateComponent<AnimatedModel>();
roboModel.Model = cache.Get<Model>("Models/Robo_01.fbx");
roboModel.SetMaterial(cache.Get<Material>("Materials/Robot_01.material"));

var animCtrl = roboNode.CreateComponent<AnimationController>();

animCtrl.PlayExclusive("walk@Models/Robo_01.fbx", 0, true);
```

Additionally, and a significant change, StringHash's are now mapped consistently across C++/C#, the marshaling is via unsigned/uint, there is a need to profile in case implicit string -> StringHash conversion is being hit hard.
